SIMPLE: philander
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Philander
<hw>Phi*lan"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fi`landros</grk> fond of men; <grk>fi`los</grk> loving +
<grk>'anh`r</grk> man.]</ety> <def>To make love to women; to play the
male flirt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You can't go <qex>philandering</qex> after her again.</q>
<rj><qau>G. Eliot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philander</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Philander
<hw>Phi*lan"der</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A lover.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Congreve.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philander</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Philander
<hw>Phi*lan"der</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A South American opossum (<spn>Didelphys philander</spn>).</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>An Australian bandicoot (<spn>Perameles
lagotis</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philanderer</ent>⟦br⟧
